Casuarina oligodon

   [648.jpg]
    Authority
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Hamamelidae:Casuarinales:Casuarinaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 648

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION: A medium to tall evergreen tree, reaching 30 m in
   height and 0.6 m in diameter. The bark is gray-brown and fissured,
   peeling off in irregular flakes. USE: It can be used for fuel and
   erosion control. Also grown as a shade crop for coffee. GROWING PERIOD:
   Perennial. COMMON NAMES: Soft yar, Yar, Sheoak. FURTHER INF: Soft yar
   is native on Papua New Guinea and is found mostly in upland vallets at
   elevations up to 2500 m or higher. It is adapted to high humidity
   throughout the year, and is sensitive to high winds. (pH is estimated
   by the compiler).

   Sources
   SOURCES
   National RC 1984 pp 64-65 [USE, TEMP, DRA, RAIN, TEXT, FER, SAL,
   LIMITS]
